4	Flood	all	video	Understanding flood early warnings (TMA)	How to read flood warnings and what each alert level means.	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=43M5mZuzHF8	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.284283+00	2026-06-12 13:20:00.284283+00	any	\N	\N
2	Flood	adults	action_guide	Maandalizi ya mafuriko kwa kaya — Household flood preparedness	Jua njia yako ya kuhama kwenda eneo la juu. — Know your evacuation route to higher ground.\nAndaa mkoba wa dharura: nyaraka, maji, tochi, sanduku la huduma ya kwanza, redio. — Prepare a go-bag: documents, water, torch, first-aid kit, radio.\nZima umeme na gesi kabla ya kuhama. — Switch off electricity and gas before evacuating.\nUsitembee wala kuendesha kwenye maji yanayotiririka — sentimita 15 zinaweza kukuangusha. — Never walk or drive through moving water — 15cm can knock you down.\nChemsha maji yote ya kunywa baada ya mafuriko. — Boil all drinking water after a flood.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.273274+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.197127+00	before	\N	\N
10	Flood	adults	action_guide	Kaa salama WAKATI wa mafuriko — Stay safe DURING a flood	Hama mara moja kwenda eneo la juu — usisubiri maelekezo. — Move immediately to higher ground — do not wait for instructions.\nUsitembee, kuogelea wala kuendesha kwenye maji ya mafuriko. — Never walk, swim or drive through flood water.\nEpuka madaraja yaliyo juu ya maji yanayokwenda kasi. — Stay off bridges over fast-moving water.\nZima umeme tu kama unaweza kufanya hivyo kwa usalama. — Disconnect electricity only if you can do so safely.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 18:07:14.273295+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.238476+00	during	\N	\N
11	Flood	adults	action_guide	Kuwa salama BAADA ya mafuriko — Be safe AFTER a flood	Rudi nyumbani tu mamlaka zitakapotangaza ni salama. — Return home only when authorities declare it safe.\nChemsha maji yote ya kunywa hadi yatakapothibitishwa kuwa safi. — Boil all drinking water until supplies are declared clean.\nPiga picha za uharibifu kwa ajili ya tathmini kabla ya kusafisha. — Photograph damage for assessments before cleaning.\nJihadhari na nyoka na vifusi katika maeneo ambayo maji yamepungua. — Watch for snakes and debris in receded areas.\nRipoti uharibifu kwa afisa wako wa kata. — Report damage to your ward officer.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 18:07:14.287523+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.256456+00	after	\N	\N
3	Flood	disabilities	action_guide	Maandalizi ya mafuriko — watu wenye ulemavu — Flood preparedness — persons with disabilities	Jisajili na afisa wa kata kwa ajili ya msaada wa kuhama. — Register with your ward officer for assisted evacuation.\nWeka vifaa vya kusaidia na dawa kwenye mfuko usiopitisha maji karibu na mlango. — Keep mobility aids and medication in a waterproof bag by the door.\nKubaliana mfumo wa kusaidiana na majirani wawili. — Agree a buddy system with two neighbours.\nWeka kadi za maandishi/picha za mawasiliano kama usemi au usikivu ni mdogo. — Keep written/picture cards for communication if speech or hearing is limited.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.279221+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.216341+00	before	\N	\N
13	Earthquake	adults	action_guide	Jiandae kabla ya tetemeko la ardhi — Prepare before an earthquake	Funga makabati, rafu na vitu vizito ukutani ili visianguke. — Secure cabinets, shelves and heavy items to the wall so they cannot topple.\nTambua sehemu salama katika kila chumba: chini ya meza imara au kando ya ukuta wa ndani. — Identify a safe spot in each room: under a sturdy table or against an interior wall.\nAndaa mkoba wa dharura: maji, dawa, tochi, betri, nyaraka muhimu na redio. — Prepare a go-bag: water, medicine, torch, batteries, key documents and a radio.\nJifunze kuzima umeme, gesi na maji nyumbani kwako. — Learn how to turn off electricity, gas and water in your home.\nPanga sehemu ambayo familia itakutana baada ya tetemeko. — Agree a family meeting point for after the quake.\nFanya mazoezi ya 'Inama, Jifunike, Ng'ang'ania' na familia yako. — Practise 'Drop, Cover, Hold On' with your family.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.701716+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.701716+00	before	\N	\N
8	Drought	adults	action_guide	Kukabiliana na vipindi virefu vya ukame — Coping with prolonged dry spells	Vuna na hifadhi maji ya mvua yanaponyesha. — Harvest and store rainwater when it falls.\nPanda mazao yanayostahimili ukame kwa ushauri wa Wizara ya Kilimo. — Plant drought-tolerant crops per Ministry of Agriculture advisories.\nLinda mifugo kwa kupunguza idadi mapema (destocking). — Protect livestock with early destocking decisions.\nFuatilia utabiri wa misimu wa TMA. — Follow TMA seasonal forecasts.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.307438+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.074694+00	before	\N	\N
9	Drought	all	video	Video: Utabiri wa Misimu Umefafanuliwa — Seasonal Forecasts Explained	Mwongozo wa Met Office kuhusu jinsi utabiri wa misimu unavyofanya kazi na jinsi ya kuutumia. — UK Met Office explainer on how seasonal forecasts work and how to use them.	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CucEP23gWfU	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.311229+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.09506+00	any	\N	\N
5	Fire	children	action_guide	Usalama wa moto kwa watoto — Fire safety for children	Nguo zikiwaka: ACHA, LALA chini, na VIRINGISHA. — If your clothes catch fire: STOP, DROP and ROLL.\nTambaa chini ya moshi. — Crawl low under the smoke.\nUsijifiche kamwe — toka nje na ubaki nje. — Never hide — get out and stay out.\nJua namba ya dharura: 114. — Know the emergency number: 114.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.293544+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.119888+00	before	\N	\N
6	Fire	adults	action_guide	Kuzuia moto nyumbani na sokoni — Home and market fire prevention	Weka kifaa cha kutambua moshi inapowezekana. — Install smoke detection where possible.\nPanga na fanya mazoezi ya njia mbili za kutokea. — Plan and practise two escape routes.\nWeka sehemu za kupikia wazi; usiache moto bila uangalizi. — Keep cooking areas clear; never leave open flames unattended.\nPiga 114 — usijaribu kuzima moto unaoenea peke yako. — Call 114 — do not fight a spreading fire yourself.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.298732+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.139566+00	before	\N	\N
7	Fire	disabilities	action_guide	Kuhama wakati wa moto — watu wenye ulemavu — Fire evacuation — persons with disabilities	Lala ghorofa ya chini inapowezekana. — Sleep on the ground floor where possible.\nWeka simu na filimbi karibu nawe usiku. — Keep a phone and whistle within reach at night.\nPanga mapema msaada wa majirani wa kuhama. — Arrange neighbour-assisted evacuation in advance.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.303007+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.153165+00	before	\N	\N
1	Flood	children	action_guide	Usalama wa mafuriko kwa watoto — Flood safety for children	Ondoka mbali na maji — usicheze kamwe kwenye maji ya mafuriko. — Move away from water — never play in flood water.\nMwambie mtu mzima mara moja maji yakiongezeka. — Tell a grown-up immediately if water is rising.\nJua mahali familia yenu inakutana. — Know your family meeting point.\nWeka mkoba wako wa shule tayari na tochi na filimbi. — Keep your school bag ready with a torch and whistle.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-12 13:20:00.266119+00	2026-06-15 22:14:05.173436+00	before	\N	\N
14	Earthquake	adults	action_guide	Wakati wa tetemeko la ardhi — During an earthquake	INAMA chini, JIFUNIKE chini ya meza imara, na NG'ANG'ANIA hadi mtetemeko ukome. — DROP to the ground, take COVER under sturdy furniture, and HOLD ON until the shaking stops.\nKaa mbali na madirisha, vioo na vitu vinavyoweza kuanguka. — Stay away from windows, glass and anything that can fall.\nUkiwa kitandani, baki hapo na linda kichwa chako kwa mto. — If you are in bed, stay there and protect your head with a pillow.\nUkiwa nje, nenda eneo wazi mbali na majengo, miti na nyaya za umeme. — If outdoors, move to an open area away from buildings, trees and power lines.\nUkiwa kwenye gari, simama kwa usalama na ubaki ndani hadi mtetemeko ukome. — If driving, pull over safely and stay inside until the shaking stops.\nUSIKIMBIE nje wakati ardhi inatetemeka. — Do NOT run outside while the ground is shaking.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.708611+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.708611+00	during	\N	\N
15	Earthquake	adults	action_guide	Baada ya tetemeko la ardhi — After an earthquake	Jiandae kwa mitetemeko ya kufuatia (aftershocks); inama, jifunike, ng'ang'ania tena. — Expect aftershocks; drop, cover and hold on again.\nKagua majeruhi na toa huduma ya kwanza; piga simu ya dharura kwa waliojeruhiwa vibaya. — Check for injuries and give first aid; call emergency services for the seriously hurt.\nUkinusa gesi, funga valvu, fungua madirisha na toka nje; usiwashe kiberiti wala swichi. — If you smell gas, shut the valve, open windows and leave; do not light a match or flip switches.\nSikiliza redio kwa taarifa rasmi na maelekezo. — Listen to the radio for official information and instructions.\nUsiingie katika majengo yaliyoharibika. — Do not enter damaged buildings.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.720374+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.720374+00	after	\N	\N
18	Earthquake	all	video	Video: Usalama wa Tetemeko — Inama, Jifunike, Ng'ang'ania — Earthquake Safety: Drop, Cover, Hold On	Mwongozo wa Shirika la Msalaba Mwekundu kuhusu hatua za usalama wakati wa tetemeko. — American Red Cross guidance on what to do during an earthquake.	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TLbOwmSadr4	\N	9	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.747335+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.747335+00	any	\N	\N
19	Cyclone	adults	action_guide	Jiandae kabla ya kimbunga — Prepare before a cyclone	Fuatilia tahadhari za TMA (Mamlaka ya Hali ya Hewa) kwenye redio na simu. — Follow TMA (Meteorological Authority) warnings on radio and phone.\nImarisha paa, milango na madirisha; kata matawi ya miti yaliyo karibu na nyumba. — Strengthen the roof, doors and windows; trim tree branches near the house.\nAndaa mkoba wa dharura: maji, chakula kisichoharibika, dawa, tochi na nyaraka. — Prepare a go-bag: water, non-perishable food, medicine, torch and documents.\nTambua kituo cha hifadhi (evacuation centre) kilicho karibu na njia ya kufika. — Identify the nearest evacuation centre and the route to reach it.\nHifadhi nyaraka muhimu kwenye mfuko usiopitisha maji. — Store important documents in a waterproof bag.\nJaza mafuta kwenye gari na chaji simu mapema. — Fuel your vehicle and charge phones early.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.754371+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.754371+00	before	\N	\N
20	Cyclone	adults	action_guide	Wakati wa kimbunga — During a cyclone	Baki ndani, mbali na madirisha; jificha katika chumba imara cha ndani. — Stay indoors, away from windows; shelter in a strong interior room.\nZima umeme na gesi kama unaelekezwa kufanya hivyo. — Switch off electricity and gas if advised to do so.\nUsitoke wakati hali inaonekana shwari ghafla — huenda ni jicho la kimbunga. — Do not go out when it suddenly calms — it may be the eye of the cyclone.\nSikiliza redio inayotumia betri kwa taarifa rasmi. — Listen to a battery radio for official information.\nKama umeelekezwa kuhama, hama mara moja kwenda kituo cha hifadhi. — If told to evacuate, leave immediately for the shelter.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.761104+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.761104+00	during	\N	\N
21	Cyclone	adults	action_guide	Baada ya kimbunga — After a cyclone	Subiri tangazo rasmi kabla ya kurudi nyumbani. — Wait for an official all-clear before returning home.\nEpuka maji yaliyofurika, nyaya za umeme zilizoanguka na barabara zilizoharibika. — Avoid floodwater, fallen power lines and damaged roads.\nUsinywe maji ya bomba hadi yathibitishwe kuwa salama; chemsha maji ya kunywa. — Do not drink tap water until confirmed safe; boil drinking water.\nKagua majeruhi na toa huduma ya kwanza. — Check for injuries and give first aid.\nPiga picha za uharibifu kwa ajili ya madai ya bima na taarifa. — Photograph damage for insurance claims and reporting.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.769577+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.769577+00	after	\N	\N
24	Cyclone	all	video	Video: Jinsi ya Kujiandaa na Kimbunga — What To Do Before & During A Cyclone	Mwongozo wa Mamlaka ya Kitaifa ya Maafa (NDMA) kuhusu usalama wa kimbunga. — National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA) guidance on cyclone safety.	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B9qR2e3xyJo	\N	9	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.792068+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.792068+00	any	\N	\N
25	Epidemic	adults	action_guide	Zuia maambukizi kabla ya mlipuko — Prevent infection before an epidemic	Nawa mikono mara kwa mara kwa maji safi na sabuni kwa sekunde 20. — Wash hands regularly with clean water and soap for 20 seconds.\nPata chanjo zinazopendekezwa na wizara ya afya. — Get the vaccinations recommended by the health ministry.\nTumia choo salama na hifadhi maji ya kunywa yaliyo safi. — Use a safe latrine and store clean drinking water.\nFuatilia taarifa rasmi za afya kutoka vyanzo vya serikali. — Follow official health information from government sources.\nAndaa sabuni, vitakasa mikono na barakoa nyumbani. — Keep soap, hand sanitiser and masks at home.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.800672+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.800672+00	before	\N	\N
26	Epidemic	adults	action_guide	Wakati wa mlipuko wa ugonjwa — During an epidemic	Nawa mikono mara kwa mara na epuka kugusa uso wako. — Wash hands often and avoid touching your face.\nFunika mdomo na pua unapokohoa au kupiga chafya. — Cover your mouth and nose when coughing or sneezing.\nKaa umbali na watu wenye dalili; vaa barakoa inapohitajika. — Keep distance from people with symptoms; wear a mask when needed.\nUkiwa na dalili, baki nyumbani na tafuta huduma ya afya mapema. — If you have symptoms, stay home and seek health care early.\nFuata maelekezo ya watoa huduma za afya na karantini. — Follow instructions from health workers and quarantine guidance.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.807661+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.807661+00	during	\N	\N
27	Epidemic	adults	action_guide	Baada ya mlipuko — Recovering after an epidemic	Endelea na usafi wa mikono na mazingira. — Continue hand and environmental hygiene.\nKamilisha dozi zote za dawa au chanjo ulizopewa. — Complete all prescribed medicine or vaccine doses.\nHudhuria vipimo vya ufuatiliaji kama ulivyoelekezwa. — Attend follow-up check-ups as advised.\nSaidia kueneza taarifa sahihi na pinga uvumi. — Help share accurate information and counter rumours.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.81557+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.81557+00	after	\N	\N
30	Epidemic	all	video	Video: Hadithi ya Kipindupindu — The Story of Cholera	Filamu fupi ya kielimu kuhusu jinsi magonjwa ya kuambukiza yanavyoenea na kuzuiwa. — A short educational film on how infectious disease spreads and is prevented (Global Health Media).	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jG1VNSCsP5Q	\N	9	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.844513+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.844513+00	any	\N	\N
31	Landslide	adults	action_guide	Jiandae kabla ya maporomoko ya ardhi — Prepare before a landslide	Tambua kama unaishi kwenye mteremko mkali au chini ya kilima — maeneo hatarishi. — Know if you live on a steep slope or below a hill — high-risk areas.\nEpuka kujenga au kulima kwenye miteremko mikali bila kinga. — Avoid building or farming on steep slopes without protection.\nPanda miti na nyasi kuimarisha udongo kwenye miteremko. — Plant trees and grass to stabilise soil on slopes.\nTengeneza mifereji ya kupitisha maji mbali na nyumba. — Build channels to divert water away from the house.\nWakati wa mvua nyingi, kuwa tayari kuhama; andaa mkoba wa dharura. — During heavy rain, be ready to evacuate; prepare a go-bag.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.852485+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.852485+00	before	\N	\N
32	Landslide	adults	action_guide	Wakati wa maporomoko ya ardhi — During a landslide	Ukisikia mlio wa udongo au kuona miti/nguzo zikitetemeka, hama mara moja. — If you hear rumbling or see trees/poles shifting, evacuate immediately.\nKimbia mbali na njia ya maporomoko, si chini yake. — Run away from the path of the slide, not below it.\nNenda eneo la juu na imara, mbali na miteremko. — Move to high, stable ground away from slopes.\nKama huwezi kutoka, jikunje na linda kichwa chako. — If you cannot escape, curl up and protect your head.\nEpuka mito na mabonde ambapo matope yanaweza kupita. — Avoid rivers and valleys where mud may flow.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.858765+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.858765+00	during	\N	\N
33	Landslide	adults	action_guide	Baada ya maporomoko ya ardhi — After a landslide	Kaa mbali na eneo la maporomoko — yanaweza kutokea tena. — Stay away from the slide area — more may follow.\nKagua majeruhi na waite wahudumu wa dharura. — Check for injuries and call emergency responders.\nEpuka maeneo yenye matope, nyaya za umeme na mabomba ya gesi yaliyokatika. — Avoid mud, downed power lines and broken gas pipes.\nRipoti njia, madaraja au mabomba yaliyoharibika kwa mamlaka. — Report damaged roads, bridges or pipes to authorities.\nSikiliza taarifa rasmi kabla ya kurudi nyumbani. — Listen to official updates before returning home.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 17:31:55.866842+00	2026-06-15 17:31:55.866842+00	after	\N	\N
