58	Volcanic Eruption	children	action_guide	Kwa watoto: mlipuko wa volkano — For children: volcanic eruptions	Volkano hutoa moto, mawe na majivu kutoka ardhini. — A volcano releases fire, rocks and ash from the ground.\nFunika pua na mdomo kwa nguo majivu yakija. — Cover your nose and mouth with cloth if ash comes.\nBaki ndani na mtu mzima na funga madirisha. — Stay inside with a grown-up and close the windows.\nUkielekezwa kuhama, nenda haraka na utulie. — If told to evacuate, go quickly and stay calm.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:56.07217+00	2026-06-15 17:31:56.07217+00	before	\N	\N
59	Volcanic Eruption	disabilities	action_guide	Watu wenye ulemavu: mlipuko wa volkano — People with disabilities: volcanic eruptions	Panga mapema usafiri wa kuhama unaopitika kwako. — Arrange accessible evacuation transport early.\nWeka barakoa za ziada kwa wenye matatizo ya kupumua. — Keep extra dust masks for those with breathing difficulties.\nHifadhi dawa za muda mrefu tayari kwenye mkoba. — Keep long-term medicines ready in your bag.\nMjulishe jirani au kiongozi mahitaji yako ya msaada. — Tell a neighbour or leader about your support needs.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:56.07852+00	2026-06-15 17:31:56.07852+00	before	\N	\N
64	Accident	children	action_guide	Kwa watoto: usalama barabarani — For children: road safety	Vuka barabara kwenye sehemu salama; angalia kulia, kushoto, kisha kulia tena. — Cross at a safe place; look right, left, then right again.\nFunga mkanda wa usalama ukiwa kwenye gari. — Wear your seatbelt in the car.\nVaa helmeti ukipanda baiskeli. — Wear a helmet when you ride a bicycle.\nUsicheze barabarani wala karibu na magari. — Do not play on the road or near vehicles.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:56.114751+00	2026-06-15 17:31:56.114751+00	before	\N	\N
65	Accident	disabilities	action_guide	Watu wenye ulemavu: usalama barabarani — People with disabilities: road safety	Tumia njia za watembea kwa miguu na sehemu za kuvukia zinazopitika. — Use pavements and accessible crossings.\nVaa au weka vitu vinavyong'aa ili uonekane usiku. — Wear or carry reflective items to be seen at night.\nPanga usafiri salama na unaopitika kwa mahitaji yako. — Plan safe, accessible transport for your needs.\nBeba taarifa za dharura za matibabu na mawasiliano. — Carry emergency medical and contact information.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 17:31:56.121655+00	2026-06-15 17:31:56.121655+00	before	\N	\N
70	Drought	adults	action_guide	Wakati wa ukame — During a drought	Tumia maji kwa uangalifu; hifadhi maji ya mvua na kutoka vyanzo salama. — Use water sparingly; store rainwater and water from safe sources.\nKinga vyanzo vya maji dhidi ya uchafuzi na uvukizi. — Protect water sources from contamination and evaporation.\nLisha mifugo kwa malisho yaliyohifadhiwa na uwapeleke kwenye maji kwa mpango. — Feed livestock with stored fodder and water them in a planned way.\nPanda mazao yanayostahimili ukame na tumia umwagiliaji mdogo. — Plant drought-tolerant crops and use small-scale irrigation.\nFuatilia ushauri wa wataalamu wa kilimo na hali ya hewa. — Follow advice from agriculture and weather experts.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.776019+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.776019+00	during	\N	\N
71	Drought	adults	action_guide	Baada ya ukame — Recovering after a drought	Panda upya mazao na ujenge tena akiba ya chakula na malisho. — Replant crops and rebuild food and fodder reserves.\nKarabati visima na miundombinu ya maji iliyoharibika. — Repair wells and damaged water infrastructure.\nSaidia kaya zilizoathirika zaidi kupata chakula na lishe. — Help the worst-affected households access food and nutrition.\nWeka mipango ya kuhifadhi maji na chakula kwa misimu ijayo. — Put in place water and food storage plans for coming seasons.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.790155+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.790155+00	after	\N	\N
74	Fire	adults	action_guide	Moto ukitokea — If a fire starts	Toka mara moja; kila sekunde ni muhimu. — Get out immediately; every second counts.\nTambaa chini ya moshi ambapo hewa ni safi zaidi. — Crawl low under the smoke where the air is cleaner.\nGusa milango kwa mgongo wa mkono kabla ya kuifungua; ikiwa moto, tumia njia nyingine. — Check doors with the back of your hand before opening; if hot, use another route.\nNguo zikiwaka: ACHA, LALA chini, na VIRINGISHA. — If your clothes catch fire: STOP, DROP and ROLL.\nUsirudi ndani kuokoa mali; piga simu ya zimamoto ukiwa nje. — Do not go back inside for belongings; call the fire brigade from outside.	\N	\N	2	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.819405+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.819405+00	during	\N	\N
75	Fire	adults	action_guide	Baada ya moto — After a fire	Usiingie jengo hadi wazima moto waseme ni salama. — Do not enter the building until firefighters say it is safe.\nKagua majeruhi na tafuta matibabu kwa waliopata moto au moshi. — Check for injuries and seek care for burns or smoke inhalation.\nZima umeme na gesi kabla ya kukagua uharibifu. — Switch off electricity and gas before inspecting damage.\nRipoti chanzo cha moto kwa mamlaka ili kuzuia tena. — Report the fire's cause to authorities to prevent a recurrence.	\N	\N	3	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.830076+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.830076+00	after	\N	\N
72	Drought	children	action_guide	Kwa watoto: ukame — For children: drought	Ukame ni kipindi kirefu bila mvua ya kutosha. — A drought is a long period without enough rain.\nTumia maji kwa uangalifu — usiyamwage bure. — Use water carefully — don't waste it.\nFunga bomba vizuri na ripoti uvujaji wa maji. — Close taps properly and report water leaks.\nNywa maji safi na salama tu. — Drink only clean, safe water.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.799801+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.799801+00	before	\N	\N
73	Drought	disabilities	action_guide	Watu wenye ulemavu: ukame — People with disabilities: drought	Hakikisha unapata maji safi ya kutosha karibu na mahali unapoishi. — Make sure you have enough clean water near where you live.\nPanga msaada wa kubeba na kuhifadhi maji kama unahitaji. — Arrange help to carry and store water if you need it.\nWeka akiba ya dawa na chakula muhimu mapema. — Keep a reserve of essential medicines and food early.\nSajili mahitaji yako na kamati ya maafa ya eneo lako. — Register your needs with your local disaster committee.	\N	\N	1	t	2026-06-15 21:37:50.810991+00	2026-06-15 21:37:50.810991+00	before	\N	\N
76	Flood	adults	action_guide	Stay safe DURING a flood	Move immediately to higher ground — do not wait for instructions.\nNever walk, swim or drive through flood water.\nStay off bridges over fast-moving water.\nDisconnect electricity only if you can do so safely.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-15 22:14:30.349977+00	2026-06-15 22:14:30.349977+00	during	\N	\N
77	Flood	adults	action_guide	Be safe AFTER a flood	Return home only when authorities declare it safe.\nBoil all drinking water until supplies are declared clean.\nPhotograph damage for assessments before cleaning.\nWatch for snakes and debris in receded areas.\nReport damage to your ward officer.	\N	\N	0	t	2026-06-15 22:14:30.35912+00	2026-06-15 22:14:30.35912+00	after	\N	\N
