13	Market fire — Kariakoo trading area	market-fire-kariakoo-trading-area-2	Overnight fire destroyed trading stalls; cause under investigation.	<p>Overnight fire destroyed trading stalls; cause under investigation.</p><p><strong>Area:</strong> Dar es Salaam &nbsp; <strong>Severity:</strong> Moderate</p><p><a href="/incident/2">View the live incident status, response and resources →</a></p>	\N	event	2026-06-17 11:39:08.201841+00	t	2026-06-17 11:24:36.520921+00	2026-06-17 11:39:08.201841+00	\N	\N	\N
16	Mining accident — Shinyanga	mining-accident-shinyanga-32	Shaft collapse at a small-scale mining site trapped several miners	<p>Shaft collapse at a small-scale mining site trapped several miners</p><p><strong>Area:</strong> Shinyanga &nbsp; <strong>Severity:</strong> Critical</p><p><a href="/incident/32">View the live incident status, response and resources →</a></p>	\N	event	2026-06-17 11:44:25.105609+00	f	2026-06-17 11:42:03.259431+00	2026-06-17 11:44:25.27773+00	\N	\N	\N
18	Government Urges All Institutions to Prepare for El Niño Impacts	government-urges-all-institutions-to-prepare-for-el-ni-o-impacts	The Government has moved to strengthen national preparedness against the potential impacts of the El Niño weather phenomenon, unveiling plans to protect lives, property and critical infrastructure following an alert issued by the Tanzania Meteorological Authority (TMA).	The Government has moved to strengthen national preparedness against the potential impacts of the El Nino weather phenomenon, unveiling plans aimed at protecting lives, property and critical infrastructure following an alert issued by the Tanzania Meteorological Authority (TMA).\n\nSpeaking in Dodoma on 25 June 2026 while closing the Disaster Management Stakeholders' Forum, the Deputy Permanent Secretary in the Prime Minister's Office (Policy, Parliament, Coordination and Persons with Disabilities), Dr. James Kilabuko, said Tanzania will continue to strengthen its disaster management systems to reduce the harm caused by hazards that cost lives, destroy property and reverse social and economic development.\n\nThe forum deliberated on the Draft National Emergency Plan for the Prevention of, and Response to, the Effects of El Nino. The Government has called on all institutions to prepare to respond to the anticipated impacts.\n\nSource: The Respondents — https://www.therespondents.co.tz/2026/06/government-draws-up-emergency-plan-as.html	\N	news	2026-06-26 18:55:58.535162+00	t	2026-06-26 18:55:58.535162+00	2026-06-26 18:55:58.535162+00	Serikali Yazitaka Taasisi Zote Kujiandaa Kukabiliana na Athari za El Niño	Serikali imesema itaendelea kuimarisha mifumo ya usimamizi wa maafa nchini ili kupunguza madhara yanayosababishwa na majanga mbalimbali ambayo yamekuwa yakigharimu maisha ya watu, kuharibu mali na kurudisha nyuma maendeleo ya kijamii na kiuchumi.	Dodoma. Serikali imesema itaendelea kuimarisha mifumo ya usimamizi wa maafa nchini ili kupunguza madhara yanayosababishwa na majanga mbalimbali ambayo yamekuwa yakigharimu maisha ya watu, kuharibu mali na kurudisha nyuma maendeleo ya kijamii na kiuchumi.\n\nKauli hiyo imetolewa leo tarehe 25 Juni, 2026 na Naibu Katibu Mkuu wa Ofisi ya Waziri Mkuu (Sera, Bunge, Uratibu na Wenye Ulemavu), Dk. James Kilabuko, wakati akifunga Jukwaa la Wadau wa Usimamizi wa Maafa lililojadili Rasimu ya Mpango wa Taifa wa Dharura wa Kuzuia na Kukabiliana na Madhara ya El Nino, Jijini Dodoma.\n\nAmesema Tanzania imeendelea kukabiliwa na matukio ya maafa yanayosababisha athari kubwa kwa wananchi na uchumi wa Taifa, hali inayolazimu kuwepo kwa maandalizi madhubuti ya kukabiliana na changamoto hizo.\n\nSerikali imezitaka taasisi zote nchini kujiandaa kukabiliana na athari zinazoweza kutokana na El Nino ili kulinda maisha ya watu, mali na miundombinu muhimu.
\.
